IAM Policy Structure:
{
    "Version": "2012-10-17", //this is always fixed
    "Id": "S3-Account-Permissions", - can be optional
    "Statement": [ //Mandatory- array of statement
        {
            "Sid": "1",
            "Effect": "Allow",
            "Principal": {
                "AWS": ["arn:aws:iam::123456789012:root"]
            },
            "Action": [
                "s3:GetObject",
                "s3:PutObject"
            ],
            "Resource": ["arn:aws:s3:::mybucket/*"]
        }
    ]
}

In AWS IAM, policies can be created and attached to users, or existing policies can be directly attached to users or groups.
Custom policies can be created and attached to individual users or groups as required.
Custom Policy: A specific AWS service can be selected, and a defined set of actions within that service can be configured along with the applicable resources, and saved as a managed or inline policy.
Custom Policy:
{
	"Version": "2012-10-17",
	"Statement": [
		{
			"Sid": "VisualEditor0",
			"Effect": "Allow",
			"Action": [
				"iam:ListUsers",
				"iam:GetUser"
			],
			"Resource": "*"
		}
	]
}
